        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Pittsburgh</placeName>, <date>Oct. 4th</date>
                <add>תרכה</add></p>
            <p><addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee>!</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Honorable Sir!</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">Having recovered<lb/> somewhat from the many<lb/> misfortunes which
                    <sic>befel</sic> me<lb/> some years ago, especially by<lb/> fire when I lost all
                I could<lb/> name my own; remembering<lb/> that I owe you yet the<lb/> subscription
                    <hi rend="underline">for 3 years</hi><lb/> for your valuable Periodical<lb/> I
                now inclose..$10,00<lb/> namely $9.00 as your due</p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>and one more for the work<lb/> Anthology of the Rabbi's<lb/> "which once was
                edited<lb/> in <placeName>Phil<hi rend="sup">a</hi></placeName> and printed on<lb/>
                the expense of—if not <sic>misstaken</sic>—<lb/> the education <sic>Socity</sic>
                in<lb/> your City.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Please enter this<lb/> to my credit and kindly<lb/> excuse my
                tardiness in<lb/> the settlement of the above<lb/> named matter.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Very respectfully yours</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">
                <persName role="author">Isaac Strouse</persName>
            </p>
            <p>P. S. If the above named work were not<lb/> among the stock of your various works</p>
            <pb n="3"/>
            <p>the newest 4 N<hi rend="sup">os.</hi> of the Occident<lb/> will do, to make up for
                the One Dol.</p>
            <pb n="4"/>
            <p>Direction: <persName role="author">Isaac Strouse</persName><lb/>
                <placeName>29 Diamond Str.<lb/> Pittsburgh</placeName>.</p>
        </body>
    </text>
